<h2>Biography</h2>
<p>Hulya Seferoglu is an Assistant Professor in the <a href="http://www.ece.uic.edu/ECE/WebHome">Electrical and Computer Engineering Department</a> of <a href="http://www.uic.edu/uic/">University of Illinois at Chicago</a>. Before joining University of Illinois at Chicago, she was a Postdoctoral Associate at <a href="http://mit.edu">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a>. She received her Ph.D. degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from <a href="http://www.uci.edu/">University of California, Irvine</a>, M.S. degree in Electrical Engineering and  Computer Science from <a href="http://www.sabanciuniv.edu/en">Sabanci University</a>, and B.S. degree in Electrical Engineering from <a href="http://www.istanbul.edu.tr/english/">Istanbul University</a>. She worked as a summer intern in AT&amp;T  Labs Research, Docomo USA Labs, and Microsoft Research, Cambridge.   </p>
